I don't recommend this place, the staff is unprofessional and rude. A white bald man at the door today was not wearing masks and was extremely rude to me. I called earlier today to reserve a table and was told that they were not making reservations and that it was only to arrive early to get a table. I arrived at 7PM, the place was empty, and he said he couldn't put me on a table because they were all booked in a very mocking and rude way. I told him about the call, and he said he doesn't know who spoke to me and that it wasn't his problem. I have never been treated so badly or seen a place with people so disliked and unprofessional. In Chicago there are many great places, with great drinks and staff who know how to treat the customer with education and respect. DON'T GO IN THIS GARBAGE PLACE! That does not respect the basic norms of sanitation and neither the customers.

I wish I could give 0 stars. My friends and I wanted to try clutch because of the good reviews, so we did. We did not get our waitresses name but she had very short brown hair/ brown eyes. We put up our sign multiple times for her to come over to us but she would just walk away, But unfortunately it does it worse. My friends and I paid half card and half cash, when she came back 85% of the bill was literally charged on to my card. All I got was a Cesar wrap and my bill was not more than $15. I don’t know the exact price of the wrap but I know it is not more than that. We asked why so much of the bill was charged on to my card and she said we didn’t give her enough cash. I saw both of my friends put in the exact amount that was needed for their part of the bill. We informed her of this and she told us she counted it 3 times and there was nothing she could do. I am not accusing her of taking the cash for herself but that’s what it seems like. I am very disappointed that I had to pay for more than I should of.

Cool bar, poor service. I had a bottle purchased on a Saturday night of the Halloween Bar Crawl. Bottle came out all nice. I had 1 drink, used the rest room and returned to my table and group of friends in the 45 minutes that I was there. The bill came out, which I paid, and was ready to purchase another bottle when I was tapped on the shoulder and asked to come to the door. The door man told me I wasn’t welcome inside because “I was too drunk and racist at the door”.  Being skeptical (as we were with a diverse group and had no problems getting seated an hour ago) I tried explaining that there might have been a misunderstanding as everyone was in costume, and that I take the accusation seriously. I asked to speak to the manager, Kristen, at the time and was told she’s too busy (she was standing at the host booth) and was threatened physically by the door man to leave and that I wasn’t allowed to stand on the sidewalk under the awning while it was pouring rain out. I tried calling the bar, no one answered. I was calm and civil throughout the entire situation. I recommend to spend your hard earned money elsewhere in the city.

Nice place, to check out, full liquor bar and large tables. Customer service is lacking because of poorly trained servers and young inexperienced bartenders. Food is good, but I wouldn't call it fine dining! High energy night club feel on Tuesday night ,ladies night promotion,  with overpriced cocktails and slow service again lacking. No parking. I caution against running up a tab, because I have had 2 bad experiences with credit card transactions,  bartenders misringig sales to the wrong account.

Great location, beautiful atmosphere, great food options and great service.  We went to watch the Bears game and it was perfect. The audio for the game is played and music during the commercials. Lots of TV's so no worries you wont have a clear view. Perfect for an upscale game experience as you wont have to compromise on eating just regular bar food. Great place to take a date who may be reluctant to watch sports. Believe me, everyone will have a great time. We tried the Deviled Eggs with the honey ham on top, which I highly recommend. The grilled chix also good and the Kale Salad, which was fantastic!

Really cool funky modern decor. The restaurant is decorated beautifully and all of the windows open like garage doors when the weather is nice. We came here for lunch around 12:30 PM on a Sunday and it was about half full. We were seated right away and and served water within minutes of being seated. The food came out quickly and the service was good. The staff wasn't the most friendly but it didn't bother me. I had the Brussel spout salad and added the tofu. The Tofu was delicious and marinated in some kind of asian dressing but there was only four little pieces - and when I say small I really mean it. For $4 I thought the portion would be a little more. That's really my only complaint about this place, though. The rest of my meal was light and enjoyable. Then menu looked good enough to come back and try something new. I'd return and take friends here to enjoy the ambiance.

Came to clutch bar last night for the first time. Didn't know it was new until I asked around before I arrived. I showed up around 11:15 and there was no line or cover. Loved that. It wasn't super crowded and I was able to snag a table for my friends and I with our drinks which were pretty strong and at a good price point. The music was decent, but the only thing I was turned off by were the transitions made by the DJ. I know that's very specific, but when dancing, I like to be able to keep the dance moves and vibes going and the DJ just wasn't doing it for me. Maybe I'll try again on another night. Has great potential!

I went to clutch bar Chicago and initially loved the atmosphere. To cut to why they’ve been given 1 star: I ordered the vegetarian burger which was typed in correctly, however, I was given a lamb burger. I do not eat meat due to health reasons. After a couple of bites, I realized my order was incorrect and told the bar staff. They said I’d get a refund and they also made the vegetarian burger over. I wasn’t feeling too well at that point so I actually handed the burger over to a friend.  Later on that week, I noticed that the refund wasn’t processed on my credit statement. I’ve called this place twice to explain the situation in detail. The first time I was told to text my information and it would be handed over to the manager on duty. The second time, I was told that they would let them know that I called for a status update. It has been two weeks and I still have not heard anything. The lack of follow up is discouraging.

Had a birthday brunch at Clutch on Sunday and we were the first table to be sat at 11am. Not sure if the kitchen wasn’t ready for a party of 10+ orders or they just dropped the ball but there was 35mins between the first food order coming out and the last. Out of 14 orders, 5 had to go back because they were cold. The waitress apologized multiple times but it wasn’t her fault and she could only do so much. No manager came over and gave an explanation for why there was so many issues so that’s why I’m writing this. Anyone with a large party should probably head somewhere else until they get their hot mess figured out.
